The paper deals with ontology engineering, which is a subfield of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of refinement operators and algorithms to repair ontologies suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.LG) and database systems (cs.DB). The need for automated methods for repairing inconsistencies also suggests a focus on software engineering (cs.SE). Finally, the empirical analysis of real-life ontologies suggests a potential overlap with natural language processing (cs.CL).
